EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 142300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING A LARGE AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE IS CENTRED 1026 OVER ROCKALL
WITH AREAS OF LOW PRESSURE CENTRED OVER EERN SCANDINAVIA AND THE FAR W OF
THE N ATLANTIC. THERE IS LITTLE CHANGE TO THE SYNOPTIC PATTERN ON FRIDAY
NIGHT OR DURING SATURDAY HOWEVER A SMALL SCALE LOW MAY BRIEFLY PASS THROUGH
S E ICELAND EARLY ON SATURDAY MORNING. THE HIGH PRESSURE CONTINUES TO PERSIST
THROUGHOUT THE WEEKEND BUT SLWY SINKS SWARDS TO REACH 1027 OVER LUNDY BY
MIDDAY SUNDAY. INTO MONDAY A CYCLONIC PATTERN MOVS EWARDS TOWARDS NERN PARTS
OF PORTPATRICK SQUEEZING THE HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE FURTHER SWARDS. MEANWHILE
A SECOND HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE FORMS OVER THE NORWEGIAN SEA. STRG WINDS ARE
EXP ACROSS FAIR ISLE ON FRIDAY EVENING EASING BY SATURDAY MORNING. HAZARDOUS
WINDS ARE NOT EXP ACROSS THE REMAINDER OF PORTPATRICK THROUGHOUT THE OUTLOOK
